# Saving Container Changes:
# If container delete or stop due to some issue, the whole content in the container get lost to overcome this problem we can save it as a image using container id.

Step-1 : Create a Docker image.

      docker pull ubuntu

Step-2 : Run the docker image.

     docker run -itd (image id)

Step-3 : Get into the container.

     docker exec -it (Container id)

Step-4 : Make some directory or install some tools and 

Step-5 : Come out from the container.

Step-6 : Run the below command to save the container changes.

      docker commit (container id) (give some name for the image)

      Example: docker commit 7a12fg container2

Step-7 : Run the image and get into the container and see if it saves or not.   
